.TH COOLERDASH 1 "November 2025" "CoolerDash 1.96" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
coolerdash \- LCD dashboard renderer for CoolerControl-compatible AIO coolers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B coolerdash
[\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR]
[\fB\-\-dual\fR]
[\fB\-\-circle\fR]
[\fB\-\-force\-display\-circular\fR]
.br
.B coolerdash
[\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR]
[\fB\-\-version\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B coolerdash
generates and uploads real-time sensor images to AIO liquid cooler LCD displays
using data from the CoolerControl daemon. It extends CoolerControl's LCD
functionality with multiple display modes, temperature visualization, and
extensive customization options.
.PP
The program supports two display modes:
.B dual mode
(simultaneous CPU+GPU display) and
.B circle mode
(alternating single-sensor display). Display shape detection automatically
adjusts layouts for circular and rectangular screens.
.PP
.B coolerdash
runs as a systemd service by default but can be executed manually for testing
and debugging purposes.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display usage information and exit.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose logging. Shows detailed information about API calls, device
detection, rendering operations, and display updates. Useful for debugging
and troubleshooting.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Display version information and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-dual
Force dual display mode (CPU and GPU simultaneously). Overrides config.json setting.
.TP
.B \-\-circle
Force circle display mode (alternating CPU/GPU every 2.5 seconds). Overrides
config.json setting.
.TP
.B \-\-force\-display\-circular
Force circular display layout (inscribe factor = 0.7071). Overrides automatic
display shape detection. Deprecated in favor of the \fBshape\fR configuration
parameter.
.SH CONFIGURATION
.B coolerdash
is configured through
.IR /etc/coolercontrol/plugins/coolerdash/config.json .
After modifying the configuration file, restart the CoolerControl service:
.PP
.RS
.nf
.B sudo systemctl restart coolercontrold.service
.fi
.RE
.SS Important Configuration Sections
.TP
.B [daemon]
CoolerControl daemon connection settings (address, password).
.TP
.B [display]
Display settings including width, height, refresh rate, brightness, orientation,
display mode (\fBdual\fR or \fBcircle\fR), and shape override (\fBauto\fR,
\fBrectangular\fR, or \fBcircular\fR).
.TP
.B [layout]
Visual layout configuration for box dimensions, bar sizes, gaps, and borders.
.TP
.B [temperature]
Temperature thresholds and color zones for visual indication.
.TP
.B [font]
Font family, sizes, and colors for temperature values and labels.
.PP
For detailed configuration options, see
.I /usr/share/doc/coolerdash/config-guide.md
or visit the project documentation online.
.SH DISPLAY MODES
.SS Dual Mode (default)
Displays CPU and GPU temperatures simultaneously in a side-by-side layout.
Recommended for all display sizes and shapes. Provides constant visibility
of both sensors.
.SS Circle Mode
Alternates between CPU and GPU display every 2.5 seconds. Optimized for
circular high-resolution displays (>240x240px) where larger text and graphics
provide better visibility.
.PP
To enable circle mode, edit
.I /etc/coolercontrol/plugins/coolerdash/config.json
and set:
.PP
.RS
.nf
"display": {
  "mode": "circle"
}
.fi
.RE
.PP
Or use the
.B \-\-circle
command-line option to temporarily override the configuration.
.SH DISPLAY SHAPE DETECTION
.B coolerdash
automatically detects whether your LCD is circular or rectangular and adjusts
the layout accordingly using an inscribe factor.
.SS Automatic Detection Rules
.TP
.B NZXT Kraken devices
Resolution-based detection:
.RS
.IP \(bu 3
≤240×240 pixels → Rectangular (inscribe factor = 1.0)
.IP \(bu 3
>240×240 pixels → Circular (inscribe factor = 0.7071)
.RE
.TP
.B Other devices
Checked against internal device database.
.TP
.B Default
Rectangular (safer fallback for unknown devices).
.SS Manual Override
You can manually override automatic detection in
.IR /etc/coolercontrol/plugins/coolerdash/config.ini :
.PP
.RS
.nf
[display]
shape = auto          # Auto-detection (default)
# shape = rectangular # Force rectangular (inscribe factor = 1.0)
# shape = circular    # Force circular (inscribe factor = 0.7071)
.fi
.RE
.PP
Priority: \fBshape\fR config > \fB\-\-force-display-circular\fR flag > auto-detection
.SH PLUGIN MODE
.B coolerdash
runs as a CoolerControl plugin, automatically managed by
.BR coolercontrold.service .
No separate service configuration is required.
.PP
Arch Linux (recommended):
.SH INSTALLATION
.SS Arch Linux (Recommended)
Using an AUR helper (e.g., yay, paru):
.PP
.RS
.nf
.B yay -S coolerdash-git
.B sudo systemctl restart coolercontrold.service
.fi
.RE
.SS All Linux Distributions
Manual installation from source:
.PP
.RS
.nf
.B git clone https://github.com/damachine/coolerdash.git
.B cd coolerdash
.B make install
.B sudo systemctl restart coolercontrold.service
.fi
.RE
.PP
The
.B make install
command automatically detects your distribution and installs required
dependencies.
.SH SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS
.TP
.B Operating System
Linux (any distribution)
.TP
.B CoolerControl
Version ≥2.2.2 (must be installed and running). See
.UR https://gitlab.com/coolercontrol/coolercontrol
.UE
for installation instructions.
.TP
.B CPU Architecture
x86-64-v3 compatible (Intel Haswell+ / AMD Excavator+ or newer)
.TP
.B LCD Display
AIO liquid cooler with LCD display (NZXT Kraken, Corsair iCUE, etc.).
All devices supported by CoolerControl/liquidctl should work.
.TP
.B Build Dependencies
gcc, make, cairo, jansson, curl, inih (automatically installed by
.BR "make install" )
.SH COOLERCONTROL SETUP
Before using
.BR coolerdash ,
configure CoolerControl:
.IP 1. 4
Open CoolerControl GUI
.IP 2. 4
Navigate to
.B Settings
→
.B "Device and Sensor"
.IP 3. 4
Select one sensor for
.B CPU
(e.g., "CPU Package")
.IP 4. 4
Select one sensor for
.B GPU
(e.g., "GPU Temperature")
.IP 5. 4
Set your LCD display output type to
.B "Image/gif"
.IP 6. 4
Save settings and restart coolerdash service
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Run manually with verbose logging
The plugin is managed by CoolerControl:
.PP
.RS
.nf
.B /etc/coolercontrol/plugins/coolerdash/coolerdash --verbose
.fi
.RE
.SS Force dual mode temporarily
.PP
.RS
.nf
.B /etc/coolercontrol/plugins/coolerdash/coolerdash --dual --verbose
.fi
.RE
.SS Force circle mode temporarily
.PP
.RS
.nf
.B /etc/coolercontrol/plugins/coolerdash/coolerdash --circle --verbose
.fi
.RE
.SS Check CoolerControl device information
.PP
.RS
.nf
.B curl http://localhost:11987/devices | jq
.fi
.RE
.SS View recent service logs
.PP
.RS
.nf
.B journalctl -u coolercontrold.service -n 50
.fi
.RE
.SH TROUBLESHOOTING
.SS Service won't start
Check CoolerControl daemon status:
.PP
.RS
.nf
.B systemctl status coolercontrold
.fi
.RE
.PP
Ensure coolercontrold is running before starting coolerdash.
.SS No devices found
Verify CoolerControl can see your device:
.PP
.RS
.nf
.B curl http://localhost:11987/devices
.fi
.RE
.PP
Check that your LCD is set to "Image/gif" mode in CoolerControl GUI.
.SS Clipping on circular display
The content appears cut off at the edges. Override display shape detection:
.PP
.RS
.nf
Edit /etc/coolercontrol/plugins/coolerdash/config.ini:
[display]
shape = circular
.fi
.RE
.PP
Then restart the CoolerControl service.
.SS Too much padding on rectangular display
Content appears too small with large margins. Override display shape:
.PP
.RS
.nf
Edit /etc/coolercontrol/plugins/coolerdash/config.ini:
[display]
shape = rectangular
.fi
.RE
